 Fri . May 19 [17] The doctor came around this afternoon and made out Donald 's and my Paper , so that is one step forward anyhow . The doctor said I was sure to be sent Home as I would not be fit for at least a year . But of cours the peopl at Weymouth have to say the Final word . We hear all sort of rumour from there . Some say that it is veri hard for a Heart case to get thro? , and other say it is just as easi . 3 chap from this ward are go down to Weymouth tomorrow . Had my Paper been made out I would most like have been go down with them . I wo n't be long tho ? now my paper are made out . [Draw of femal kneel in front of fire , titl " Memori of 19 Pitt St . Nth Sydney ] Sat . May 18 Bill Beard came to see me today and brought my Kit Bag . He has left the Officer 's Mess and await a Board for Lung Troubl . Wrote to Ern Harvey and Mrs Sam Ibbs . Must write Nell and Mother tomorrow .
